userMessage: Current altitude 3000 ft, speed 90 kt. What should I do?
sallyResponse:
Increase throttle to full and pitch up to Vr (55 KIAS) for rotation. Once rotated, engage AP in heading hold and vertical speed mode with a target climb rate of +700 fpm.

COMMANDS_JSON: [{"command":"THROTTLE_SET","value":100}, {"command":"AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET","value":-25}, {"command":"AP_HDG_HOLD"}, {"command":"AP_VS_VAR_SET","value":700}]

RECOMMEND: Considering there's no previous data, initial values will be conservative to ensure stability.

COMMANDS_JSON: [{"command":"THROTTLE_SET","value":100}, {"command":"AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET","value":-25}, {"command":"AP_MASTER"}, {"command":"HEADING_BUG_SET","value":270}]

RECOMMEND: Start by setting a higher throttle during takeoff roll to achieve better acceleration and ground handling. Consider enriching the mixture slightly before Vr. Ensure smooth rotation at Vr and maintain wings level.

COMMANDS_JSON: [{"command":"THROTTLE_SET","value":75}, {"command":"MIXTURE_SET","value":100}]
